MESSAGE.value:
Update feature flag and clean up geometry primitives
Updated feature flags from "opencascade_rs" to "occ" for consistency. Also, code for geometry primitives like Cube, Cylinder, Torus, etc., has been cleaned up. This involved creating a new module "basic", introducing Arc for shared structures and replacing Shape structures with OccSharedShape where needed.

Refactor geometry primitives and improve feature flags
The feature flag has been consistently updated from "opencascade_rs" to "occ". In addition, the code for geometry primitives like Cube, Cylinder, Torus, etc., has been refactored. This has involved creating a new module "basic", introducing shared structures with Arc, and replacing Shape structures with OccSharedShape where needed.

Refactor geometry primitives computation and cleanup
Updated the computation in lpyramid.rs and cleanup in category.rs to prevent single-point situations. Maximized division result to 0.001 for better reliability. Fixed minor spacing issues for consistency and readability. Slight adjustments were made in workspace.xml, primarily changes related to Cargo and test settings.

Update geometry computation and cleanup code
Refactored geometry primitives computation in lpyramid.rs and did cleanup in category.rs to avoid single-point situations. Optimized division result for better reliability and made minor formatting adjustments for readability. Modifications were also made in workspace.xml mainly in relation to Cargo and test settings.

Refactor geometry computation and tidy up the code
This commit includes code refactoring for the computation of geometry primitives in the lpyramid.rs file. It also addresses cleaning up in category.rs to prevent single-point scenarios. The division result was optimized for improved reliability and readability-enhancing formatting adjustments were applied. Changes in workspace.xml related mainly to Cargo and test settings.

Simplify and refactor geometry computations in category.rs
This commit optimizes the geometry computations in category.rs by simplifying the logic and refactoring the existing code. Changes include removing unnecessary variables and duplicated code, reducing the complexity of if-else conditions, and introducing LCylinder for better manageability. Minor adjustments in workspace.xml for Cargo and test settings were also made.

Update geometry handling logic in category.rs and resolve.rs
This commit refines geometry computation in category.rs and increases iteration limits in resolve.rs. It simplifies the logic in category.rs to enhance readability, while enhancing error resiliency in resolve.rs. Changes to workspace.xml pertain to updating group and task settings.

Add HVAC calculations and update geometry definition in pdms_shape.rs
This update includes HVAC-related calculations in new SurQL files and adjusts the geometry definition in pdms_shape.rs. Target architecture conditions and additional functions are introduced for differentiating WASM from non-WASM builds. The commit also includes several new files contributing to HVAC computation logic, as well as a batch file for running the database scripts.

Update geometry definition and add HVAC calculations
The code has been updated to include HVAC-related calculations in new SurQL files and make adjustments to the geometry definition in pdms_shape.rs. Several new files contributing to HVAC computation logic are added, while distinguishing WASM from non-WASM builds through target architecture condition checks. Additionally, a new batch file is created for running the database scripts.

Refactor attribute value handling and improve SQL queries
Made adjustments to the handling of the 'RefU64Type' in 'NamedAttrValue' to improve string representation. Optimized SQL queries in 'graph.rs' by revising criteria and introduced 'inst.rs' for query helper functions. In addition, a minor update was made in 'pdms_types.rs' to include an empty vector initialization

Refactor attribute value handling and improve SQL queries
Made adjustments to the handling of the 'RefU64Type' in 'NamedAttrValue' to improve string representation. Optimized SQL queries in 'graph.rs' by revising criteria and introduced 'inst.rs' for query helper functions. In addition, a minor update was made in 'pdms_types.rs' to include an empty vector initialization handling and improved performance.

Update handling of attribute values and optimize SQL queries
The commit improves the string representation of 'RefU64Type' in 'NamedAttrValue'. Changes in 'graph.rs' also enhance the efficacy of SQL queries with revised criteria. Additionally, enhancements in 'pdms_types.rs' aid in vector handling.

Refactor attribute handling and optimize SQL queries
Revised the handling of 'RefU64Type' in 'NamedAttrValue' for improved string representation. Optimized SQL queries in 'graph.rs' for increased performance and updated vector handling in 'pdms_types.rs'.

Add GeomPtsQuery structure in inst.rs
Introduced a new structure, GeomPtsQuery, in inst.rs, which contains reference number, world transform, and a vector of points group data. The structure has been marked to support serialization, deserialization and debugging functionalities.
fix wire cal

Improve wire calculation and calibrations
This commit focuses on enhancing the wire calculation and calibration methods. Debugging statements have been streamlined for efficiency and areas of the code have been modified to handle edge cases more effectively. This includes addition of aabb center, automated filtering of points, location removal, and improving vector normalization. Unnecessary debug and println lines have also been removed to clean up the code. Furthermore, several tests were added to verify and provide coverage on the updated parts of the code.

Modify wire calculation and improve calibration
The commit enriches wire calculation and calibration methods. Code has been optimized to manage exceptions more accurately. Debug and println commands have been cleansed for better code readability. In addition, the implementation now includes automated filtering of points, removal of locations, and improved vector normalization. Several tests have also been incorporated to ensure appropriate coverage for the modifications.

Update test query, schema syntax and import changes
Test query in the suite has been updated. Changes have been made in 'group_by_cata_hash.surql', 'query_full_attmap_by_refno.surql' schemas. BTreeMap has been imported in 'pdms_types.rs'. All these changes aim to optimize the test suites and query structures of the system.

Update schema syntax and query optimization
Revised query syntax in 'query_full_attmap_by_refno.surql' and 'mdb.rs' for improved performance. Adjustments specifically target retrieving DBNO and UDNA values. These adjustments aim to enhance system efficiency.

Refactor queries and schemas for performance improvement
Updated the syntax for 'query_full_attmap_by_refno.surql' and made necessary changes in 'mdb.rs' to optimize query performance. Key focus was on efficient retrieval of DBNO and UDNA values, contributing to the overall system efficiency.

Add new function file, refactor schemas and property values
A new function file `common.surql` was introduced. Query in `query_full_attmap_by_refno.surql` was updated to improve retrieval of specific property values. Changes also include enhancements in workspace configuration and settings.

Remove test_gen_wire_3.step file
This commit removes the step file related to the 3D test generation of wire. The file was cluttering the directory and its use was no longer necessary for current and future project operations. All project operations continue to function as expected without this file.

Add parse_ori_str_to_mat function and update test_spatial.rs
Added an inline function, parse_ori_str_to_mat, in dir_tool.rs which parses the orientation string to a Mat3 result. Several updates were also made to the test_spatial.rs file. These include creation of a new test_transform module with several new tests, and minor revisions in existing tests. Additionally, related updates were made in spatial.rs, and unused data was removed from workspace.xml.

Add wire generation tests and update debug messaging
New wire-generation tests have been added to the test suite in 'test_wire.rs'. Accompanying this, debug messages output during acceleration tree computations have been commented. Spatial function logic in 'spatial.rs' was updated for zero-length direction vectors. Misc changes in '.idea/workspace.xml' correspond to the latest run configurations and tasks.
